CNCP v1 23063
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7389: Spread on readonly object returns empty object in Safari 12 & 13",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:16.265545+00:00",
  "text": "Spread on readonly object returns empty object in Safari 12 & 13\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.45\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nNote that in e.g. Safari 14, the text is rendered as:\r\n> { \"msg\": \"Hello World!\" }\r\n> { \"msg\": \"Hello World!\" }\r\n\r\nWhile in Safari 12 & 13 it is rendered as:\r\n> { \"msg\": \"Hello World!\" }\r\n> {}\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThat the text is rendered in Safari 12 & 13 as:\r\n> { \"msg\": \"Hello World!\" }\r\n> { \"msg\": \"Hello World!\" }\r\n\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe spread of `readonlyObj` is returning `{}`.\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "browser specific"
  ],
